content:
Add the Omni-Channel Component to a Lightning App

To give agents easy access to Omni-Channel, add it where they work—in a Lightning app.

Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Omni-Channel is available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

You can also add Omni Supervisor to the Classic Service Console. However, Omni-Channel works best with Lightning apps.

Add the Omni-Channel component to your Lightning app to route work to agents in a flash.

Add the Omni-Channel Component to the Classic Console

After you get Omni-Channel all set up for your organization, it’s time to add the Omni-Channel component to the Salesforce classic console so that your agents can start receiving work.

Control Visible Work Item Details in Omni-Channel with Compact Layouts

Ever wanted to customize the information that your agents see when they get a new work item in Omni-Channel? You can! Just customize primary compact layout for that work item’s object.
title: Adding Omni-Channel to Salesforce
